51. Max Weber Forum/South Asia Institute (SAI) of Heidelberg University Fellowship
Deadline: June 4, 2025
Focus: ethnology, history, political science, economics, geography, modern languages and literatures of South Asia as well as cultural and religious history of South Asia.
Eligibility: young researchers from India, Nepal, Pakistan, Sri Lanka or Bangladesh who wish to establish and develop a research collaboration with the SAI. 
Website: SAI Fellowship
Benefits: scholarship includes reimbursement of international travel expenses of up to EUR 1,500, payment of rental costs and a monthly scholarship installment of EUR 1,200.

52. ADEL Atlantic Dialogue Emerging Leaders Program 
Deadline: June 15, 2025
Focus: interest in issues affecting Wider Atlantic relations, and a clear commitment to global, Atlantic, and/or local engagement.
Eligibility: rising changemakers from the Africa, North/Central/South America, Europe, or the Caribbean
Website: https://www.policycenter.ma/page/call-applications-atlantic-dialogues-emerging-leaders-program-2025
Benefits: Fully funded,with commencement in-person at Rabat, Morocco 


53. William P. Fuller Fellowship in Peacebuilding
Deadline: June 1, 2025
Focus: actively advancing peace through research, advocacy, policymaking, or community practice 
Eligibility: For early and mid-career professionals from Asia and the Pacific (Must be a citizen of one of the following countries or regions: Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Bhutan, Cambodia, Indonesia, Japan, Laos, Malaysia, Mongolia, Myanmar, Nepal, Pacific Islands, Pakistan, Philippines, Singapore, Sri Lanka, Thailand, Timor-Leste, Vietnam)
Website: https://asiafoundation.org/call-for-applications-2025-fuller-fellowship-in-peacebuilding/
Benefits: Virtual program + TAF will provide each fellow with a flexible professional development grant to support their individually tailored projects or advance their professional goals.
